    "This is partly because some of the considered datasets include only one user and partly because in real deployments the small Pool of Examples used by few-shot ADL-LLM may be collected from the target home during the system's initial deployment.",
    "Nevertheless, no window of sensor data in the training set appears in the test set, ensuring that the model is not exposed to data leakage.",
    "Note that the supervised baselines would likely exhibit even lower performance using a user-based split; hence the advantage of zero-shot ADL-LLM would be even clearer.",
    "Simulating data scarcity scenarios.In order to evaluate the effectiveness of few-shot ADL-LLM we consider different labeled data availability scenarios to populate the pool: 100%, 50%, 25%, 10%, and 5% of the training set.",
    "In these settings, the supervised baselines use the available labeled data for training."
